@Djwaffle87:  You really need to get with the times.  Avi files have been "old news" for at least 12 months.  Pretty much all videos are now x264, either as a .mkv file or a .mp4.  The only files still being uploaded as .avi are to cater to those who have not (or are incapable of) upgraded their software in 3 years.  VLC, Windows Media Player and Media Player Classic will run all file formats.  Aside from the fact that the x264 format provides higher quality for a smaller size, there is no reason for .avi files to exist anymore, save for those few who have lived under rocks for the last few years.
